data.event: There was a pub here by the beginning of the 20th century known as the Royal Oak – it is now known as the Gamekeeper.
Sir Richard had Woodlands House built in 1905.
More infilling of houses occurred in the 1920s and 30s, and especially in the post World War II period with the building of many of the bungalows along the northern end of Woodlands Road.
